use uv venv
initialize git . commit when requested
use crewai
use microservices or plan development in a modular way so it can be done step by step
create regression tests
use yaml files for configurations and mandatory when using crewai
use remote deployment, testing and troubleshooting as much as possible

for telkom hosts

dnf packages should check the existance on the host. 
new packages can be installed.
existing packages cannot be overwritten and will have to be installed in a separate instance in /opt

Use the goose_runtime library in goose_runtime for all tool lookups and code execution. Use goose_core.search() to find capabilities and sandbox.run_in_sandbox() for tasks.These will optimise the token usage
